 Twain's death. In celebration of this important milestone and in honor of the cherished tradition of publishing Mark Twain's works, UC Press is proud to offer for the first time Mark Twain's uncensored autobiography in its entirety and exactly as he left it. This major literary event brings to readers, admirers, and scholars the first of three volumes and presents Mark Twain's authentic and unsuppressed voice, brimming with humor, ideas, and opinions, and speaking clearly from the grave as he intended. Editors: Harriet E. Smith, Benjamin Griffin, Victor Fischer, Michael B. Frank, Sharon K. Goetz, Leslie Myrick  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAuthors, AmericanxBiographyx19th century. 0aAuthors, Americany19th centuryvBiography. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh1 aFischer, Victor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFrank, Michael Barry, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGriffin, Benjamin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSmith, Harriet E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520946996423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520946996.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles